        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 4:30AM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 430 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles south of Pullman, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pullman and Colton.

This includes the following highways...
U.S. Highway 95 in Idaho between mile markers 336 and 341.
U.S. Highway 195 in Washington between mile markers 7 and 20.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
